{
  "id": "2fbd2a82-14ba-4e6e-90f6-e0c34f0f912c",
  "title": "Plan-before-fan-out bracket: gated planning node before breakdown",
  "description": "Make planning a first-class, reviewable, gated node in the DAG, sequenced before the implementation fan-out. A breakable container C is bracketed by a planning node P (agent plan-quality gate) and a breakdown node B (deterministic coverage-preview gate via validate --scope), with the impl subgraph spliced into the C->B link as a spine (P > B > impl > C). Front-end counterpart to epic 94d26c42's done-transition coverage enforcement.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- [hard] Breakable container scaffolds to C->P (plan-quality gate on P); the breakdown step splices the impl subgraph and B into a reduced C->impl->B->P spine, correctly typed.\n- [hard] Breakdown gate blocks when drafted children leave a [hard] criterion uncovered, evaluated transitively over the impl interior (exit 4).\n- [hard] Coverage traversal is transitive by default; child-type-exclude excludes bracket nodes and halts descent at them.\n- [hard] jit plan <existing> retrofits a container, moving upstream deps onto P.\n- [hard] Demonstrated on SDD (epic) and research (goal, no epic) with no methodology strings in Rust.\n- jit-breakdown and project-lead drive plan->review->breakdown->coverage->implement; steering suite regression-tests it.\n\nDesign: dev/active/planning-bracket-design.md",
  "state": "done",
